1
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,800
We should have breakfast together
我们应该一起吃个午饭

2
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:17,800
Did you bring the pantsuit with you?
你带了套装过来吗？

3
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,000
What suit?
什么套装？

4
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,200
The new one
新的那套

5
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,800
Sorry kid, i forgot it
对不起，我忘了

6
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:45,900
Please bring another place setting
到别处去弄吧

7
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,900
Good morning Mr Gruhner
早上好，格努先生

8
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:07,500
I've got a job for you
我给你找了份工作

9
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:15,300
Those are 100,000 Marks. For that money
you will get documents that I need
这是十万马克，用这些钱拿到我需要的文件吧

10
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:18,400
You'll contact this address
联系这个地址

11
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:22,000
Cameron...
卡梅隆

12
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:24,700
Should you have problems, call me
如果有问题，联系我

13
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:30,900
You don't have to be worried...
I know Cameron... he's often worked for me
你不用担心，我了解卡梅隆，他经常为我工作

14
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:35,700
What's it about?
关于什么的文件？

15
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,200
Before I forget...
趁我还没忘记

16
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:40,500
This matter stays between us, for your own good
这事情是关乎我们两个人，但是对你好

17
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,000
I trust you
我信任你

18
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:44,600
You could be back the day after tomorrow
你可以后天回来

19
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:47,900
But get a good night's sleep before
之前好好睡一觉

20
00:06:57,900 --> 00:06:59,400
Have you got fire?
有火吗？

21
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:03,000
Laura will accompany you
劳拉会跟你一块儿

22
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:26,100
Aren't you tired at all?
你不累吗？

23
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:42,900
Who is Cameron?
谁是卡梅隆？

24
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:44,200
What did he tell you?
他跟你说了些什么？

25
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,800
So you know about it...
这么说你知道他

26
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,400
We have to cash this check
必须把这支票换成现金

27
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,700
We'll live in our flat in Rome
我们会住在罗马的公寓

28
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,000
Give it to me
给我

29
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,500
I'm gonna draw some cash my self
我要自己拿一些现金

30
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:07,800
Dad's often in Rome
我父亲经常在罗马

31
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:19,700
Fuel it completely
加满油

32
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:43,300
Monika? Frank...
莫妮卡？我是弗兰克

33
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,200
I gotta talk to you
我要和你谈谈

34
00:08:45,500 --> 00:08:48,700
We're on our way to Munich...
I'm going to call you in the evening
我们在去慕尼黑的路上  晚上我会打给你

35
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:56,600
- Keep the change
- Thank you
不用找了  谢谢

36
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,400
Well, porgy?
呃，调皮？

37
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:31,700
- Taxi, please
- Yes?
出租车  谁？

38
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,700
Immediately
马上

39
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:42,100
The taxi... think of something for tonight
出租车来了，想想今晚的事情吧

40
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,800
I want to wear my new dress
我想穿我的新衣服

41
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,300
In half an hour
半小时后

42
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:40,000
I'm driving to Rome tomorrow
我明天开车去罗马

43
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:44,800
We have got 100.000 Marks
现在有十万马克

44
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:54,400
I suppose you're not interested in how
i got to the money....
我想你不会对我是怎么得到这钱感兴趣的

45
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:56,400
You got it from Gruhner
你从格努那儿拿到的

46
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:10,400
Of course Gruhner told you all about it
last night...
昨晚格努肯定告诉了你一切

47
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,000
Don't be silly
别傻了

48
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:20,000
- It took me the whole night to convince him of giving you the job
- We're going to Las Vegas with the money
我花了一整晚才说服他给你这份工作   我们要用这笔钱去拉斯维加斯

49
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,100
No, Frank
不，法兰克

50
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:25,700
We've been waiting for this opinion for months
我们已经等了几个月了

51
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:29,800
- What did Gruhner tell you?
- Nothing
格努都跟你说了什么？  什么都没说

52
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:35,200
Gruhner wants to make business with Romania
格努想在罗马尼亚做生意

53
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:39,700
At the moment a Romanian trade delegation is
negotiating with an Italian car company
现在一个罗马尼亚贸易代表团正和一家意大利汽车公司在谈判

54
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:42,300
It's about some licenses
是关于一些许可证的事

55
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:44,600
Gruhner wants to underbid the Italians
格努想比意大利人出的价格低

56
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:47,800
For that he needs the papers about the negotiations
他想要的文件正是关于谈判的

57
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:50,900
Cameron will give them to you in Rome
卡梅隆将会在罗马把文件给你

58
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,600
The documents are worthless for us
那些文件对我们没什么用

59
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:08,100
Aren't 100,000 enough for you?
十万马克对你来说够吗?

60
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,200
No, they aren't
不

61
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:19,400
I know an American industrialist
我认识一个美国的实业家

62
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,400
He's also interested in Romania
他也对罗马尼亚的生意感兴趣

63
00:14:21,700 --> 00:14:24,400
- He's gonna pay a lot for those documents
- How do you know him?
他打算为那些文件出很多钱  你是怎么知道他的？

64
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:26,900
He's in Acapulco... I'm going to fly
there tomorrow
他在阿尔普尔科，我明天要飞到那儿

65
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:29,800
You'll follow me as soon as you
got the documents
你拿到了那些文件就跟着我

66
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:32,400
How much is he gonna pay?
他打算付多少？

67
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:34,500
Half a million
五十万

68
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:36,800
Dollars?
美金？

69
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:40,100
That's money, Frank
那是钱啊，弗兰克

70
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,000
Too much
太多了

71
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:49,100
They can't be worth that much
他们不可能值那么多

72
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:52,700
I don't trust the whole thing...
How well do you know that American?
我不相信这整件事  你对那个美国人了解多少？

73
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,700
He does what I tell him...
他对我言听计从

74
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:58,400
- Does he love you?
- Maybe
他爱你吗？  也许吧

75
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:00,500
That's not my business
那不关我事

76
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,800
That's our chance
这是我们的机会

77
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,600
I don't plan to miss it
我不想错过它

78
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:21,200
It's 10,000 km to Acapulco
到阿尔普尔科有一万公里

79
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,400
100,000 Marks...
十万马克

80
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:27,300
That feels good
感觉不错

81
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,300
Who is that American?
那个美国人究竟是谁？

82
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:04,500
I promised Laura to go out with her...
She's got a new dress
我答应和劳拉一块儿去  她穿着新衣服

83
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:07,500
Be nice to her... she mustn't get suspicious
对她温柔点，不能让她起疑心

84
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:09,200
She's coming with me to Rome...
她和我一起去罗马

85
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:14,800
10 pm in the scotch-bar, I'll be there with Laura
晚上十点到苏格兰酒吧，我和劳拉会在那儿

86
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:20,800
Gruhner doesn't trust you
格努并不信任你

87
00:19:57,500 --> 00:20:00,200
Get out of that car!
离开那辆车！

88
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,200
Not so tired
Get out!
别装了  出来！

89
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:04,700
We should talk a bit
我们应该稍微谈谈

90
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:15,500
Why so hastily?
为什么这么匆忙？

91
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:18,200
No time for friends?
没给朋友留点时间吗？

92
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:26,100
We just mean well...
我们只是想

93
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:27,700
What do you want?
你想要什么？

94
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,900
We were missing you...
我们不了解你了

95
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:37,900
- I'm sure you got your checkbook with you, don't you?
- He he, Markus, the boy's got humour
我确定你随身带着支票本，是吗？  呵呵，马库斯，这小子还有点儿幽默嘛

96
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:39,800
Or cash?
还是现金？

97
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:49,100
Well, what's that supposed to mean?
这是什么意思呢？

98
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:54,400
You don't want to make your friends unhappy,
do you?
你不想使你的朋友们扫兴吧，是吧？

99
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:58,600
Give me that
把那个给我

100
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:00,600
You could hurt yourself
你会伤到你自己的

101
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:04,000
Now shot...come on, shoot!
开枪啊，来吧，开枪

102
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:06,100
Why don't you shoot?
为什么不开枪呢？

103
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:08,800
Want me to show you how to do it?
想让我给你示范一下怎么开枪吗？

104
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,700
But don't be surprised about the bang
但是不要对枪响感到惊讶哦

105
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:22,900
You're disappointing us
你太让我们失望了

106
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:27,200
Really disappointing us...
真的让我们失望

107
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:29,900
Do you treat friends that way?
你用那种方式对待朋友吗？

108
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:31,900
Now you're high
现在你爽了吧

109
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:35,900
Good...
好

110
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,700
Thank you
谢谢

111
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:07,200
Careful...
小心

112
00:23:09,700 --> 00:23:11,100
You pig!
死猪

113
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:15,000
Dirty? Did you get beaten up?
脏衣服？你被打败了？

114
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:16,800
What's up?
那又怎么样？

115
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:18,800
Get away from here!
离开这里

116
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:21,000
Calm, stay calm
冷静，保持冷静

117
00:23:23,700 --> 00:23:25,300
Your coat is really dirty
你的大衣真是太脏了

118
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:30,000
I just wanted my boys to be nice to you and
wish you a good evening
我只是要求我的朋友们对你好一点，希望你有个美好的夜晚

119
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:33,700
How unfortunate
真是太不幸了

120
00:23:57,100 --> 00:23:58,300
I'm out
我退出

121
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:02,100
How nice
多好玩啊

122
00:24:02,300 --> 00:24:04,000
I don't have anything to do with you anymore
我不会跟你一起做任何事情了

123
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:10,400
You want to say you got Gruhner's
little daughter now
你是想说你得到了格努的女儿了么

124
00:24:12,100 --> 00:24:13,100
And don't need us anymore
再也不需要我们了

125
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:14,200
Exactly
正是

126
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:23,800
You've become genteel
你快成上流社会了

127
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,100
Very fancy
真花哨

128
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:31,500
Take you hands off me!
把你的手拿开

129
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:35,900
Ah, I'm sorry
噢，对不起

130
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:39,500
I forgot you had nothing to do with us anymore
我忘了你与我们再没有任何关系了

131
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:41,300
Do with your stuff what you want to do
滚去做你想做的事情去吧

132
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:42,900
Smoke it yourselves if you want to
如果你想，自己抽烟去

133
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:47,300
And you think Daddy Gruhner will be happy
when he learns that his future son-in-law...
你认为岳父格努会高兴吗

134
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:49,200
has been involved in such ugly things
当他知道他未来的女婿卷入这种肮脏的事情中

135
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:50,900
You're that smart, aren't you?
你是聪明人，对吧？

136
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:53,200
Leave Gruhner alone
离格努远点儿

137
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:54,900
Or you're all finished
否则你完了

138
00:24:58,800 --> 00:25:00,100
That was a pretty clever idea of you
你这个想法很聪明

139
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:01,900
You're really using your brain
看来你现在真的开始动脑子了

140
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,000
That's what i like about you
这就是我为什么喜欢你的原因

141
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,300
Did we scare you?
我让你害怕吗？

142
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:12,200
I can understand you
我了解你

143
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:16,400
I wouldn't feel well in your situation either
如果我处在你的处境下，也会感觉很糟糕

144
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:18,700
Next time it's your turn
下次就轮到你了

145
00:25:20,300 --> 00:25:23,700
Listen Frank, who would say things like that
Why so aggressive?
听着，弗兰克，谁会像你这样说话呢，为什么这么咄咄逼人

146
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:27,700
Nobody wants to hurt you, it was a little joke
by the boys, they like that
没人想伤害你，那只不过是朋友们开的小玩笑而已，他们喜欢那样

147
00:25:27,900 --> 00:25:28,900
Just for training
只是为了训练你

148
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:32,100
- Maybe I'll invite them to the wedding
- Here you go
或许我会邀请他们参加婚礼  又来了

149
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:34,200
Finally you're getting reasonable
最终你会变得讲理的

150
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:37,800
We always understood each other
I always had a soft spot for you
我们总是互相理解  我对你情有独钟

151
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:40,300
Your tendency towards the better world,
to all nice things
你倾向于更好的世界  一切美好的东西

152
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:42,900
You know how to deal with people like Gruhner
你懂得像格努一样处理人际关系

153
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:44,600
That's what I like about you
这也是我为什么喜欢你的原因

154
00:25:45,100 --> 00:25:47,400
I can give you some lessons if you want
如果你想，我可以给你上上课

155
00:25:48,900 --> 00:25:52,000
You shouldn't forget your old friends when
you're rich and happy
当你有钱快乐的时候不应忘掉老朋友

156
00:25:52,100 --> 00:25:53,700
Especially if you owe them money
尤其是你欠他们钱的时候

157
00:25:54,300 --> 00:25:58,000
Why don't you talk to Gruhner?
Maybe he will give you a check
为什么你不同格努谈谈？  也许他会给你张支票

158
00:25:58,500 --> 00:26:01,600
No, that wouldn't be a good idea,
you wouldn't want trouble with your girl
不，那不是个好主意  你不会想要你的女人有麻烦吧

159
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:05,600
You see how considerate the boys are,
nobody hurt your pretty little face
你看那男孩多体贴  没人会伤害你那漂亮的脸蛋

160
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:07,000
Fine
好吧

161
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:08,600
You'll get the money
你会拿到钱的

162
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:10,600
But only if you leave me alone
只要你离开我

163
00:26:11,100 --> 00:26:12,000
That sounds good
听起来不错

164
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:14,500
We leave you alone as long as you pay
只要你付钱，我们不打搅你

165
00:26:16,300 --> 00:26:16,900
Ah
呵

166
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:19,200
You've planned that great
你计划的不错嘛

167
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:23,900
That way we never loose track of each other
or do you want to lose track of each other?
那样的话我们不会失去联系   你想跟我们失去联系吗？

168
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:29,000
Such a little scandal, that would be very bad for you,
that would be very bad for us all
这样一个小丑闻会对你非常不利  对我们所有人都不好

169
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,000
Surely for you
对你当然不好

170
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:37,100
Maybe we can even cooperate, not now, but later,
也许我们甚至可以合作，不是现在，迟点儿

171
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:40,200
when you reached a nice position in Gruhner's
company, you understand?
当你在格努的公司有个好的位置时，你明白吗？

172
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:42,300
You want to switch to the car-business?
你想改做汽车生意？

173
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:46,000
We hope you won't fail, we are a bit worried, you know
我希望你别失败，你知道，我们有点担心

174
00:26:46,100 --> 00:26:48,700
marrying her isn't enough, you gotta assert yourself,
单单与她结婚并不够，你必须保全自己

175
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:50,100
We'll see...
我们将会看到

176
00:26:50,500 --> 00:26:52,400
What do you want to do against Gruhner?
你想做什么来反对格努？

177
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:54,300
Who do you think you are?
你以为你是谁？

178
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:57,100
Nothing but small...
没什么，除了小小的

179
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:58,800
...lousy...crooks
差劲骗术

180
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:02,100
You know your limits at least
你终于知道了你的能耐

181
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,500
Why aren't you dressed?
为什么没有穿好

182
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:13,500
What happened to you?
你怎么了？

183
00:27:13,700 --> 00:27:15,400
- Why?
- Where've you been?
为什么？  你到哪儿去了？

184
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:17,200
I did something for your father
我为你爸做了点事

185
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:18,500
What happened?
发生了什么？

186
00:27:20,100 --> 00:27:21,200
Nothing
没什么

187
00:27:21,300 --> 00:27:23,900
I got a headache, i don't want to go out
我有点儿头痛，我不想出去了

188
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:25,600
Then I'll go out on my own
那我只有独自出去了

189
00:27:25,900 --> 00:27:27,000
We'll go out in Rome
到了罗马我们再出去

190
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:29,300
I want to wear my new dress today
今天我想穿我的新衣服

191
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:32,300
Say, is there anything else on
your mind besides clothes?!
听，除了衣服，你的脑子里还有别的吗？！

192
00:27:33,100 --> 00:27:34,300
Sometimes..
有时候有的

193
00:27:40,300 --> 00:27:41,300
What's that?
那是什么？

194
00:27:41,700 --> 00:27:43,300
I thought you had a headache
我以为你有点儿头疼

195
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:45,500
I have to drive the whole day tomorrow
我明天得开一整天车

196
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:48,200
Why aren't we taking a plane?
为什么我们不坐飞机去呢？

197
00:27:48,900 --> 00:27:50,300
Why do I actually have to go to Rome?
为什么我一定要去罗马？

198
00:27:51,300 --> 00:27:52,700
Because my father wants you to
因为我爸想要你去

199
00:27:53,500 --> 00:27:56,500
If i think about it, I actually don't feel like
going to Rome
如果仔细想想  我真的不想去罗马

200
00:27:58,800 --> 00:27:59,800
I think you are
我认为你想

201
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:02,200
Why?
为什么？

202
00:28:02,700 --> 00:28:05,200
Your father should get his hands dirty himself
你爸应该自己干这破事

203
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:07,500
Good, go, call him
好啊，去，跟他打电话

204
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:10,500
Tell him that you're no longer interested
in the job
告诉他你对这工作不感兴趣了

205
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:14,300
He will draw consequences and  give the job
to someone who will do it better than you
他会好好想想，然后将这工作给比你干的好的人

206
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:17,500
Did he say that?
他这么说过吗？

207
00:28:19,300 --> 00:28:22,200
It could be possible that he's got a lot
planned with you
他倒是有可能在你身上有很多计划

208
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:24,500
I won't let your father buy me
我不会让你的父亲拿钱买我的

209
00:28:25,500 --> 00:28:27,900
You're right, I have no idea about such things
你是对的，我对这事没什么想法

210
00:28:29,400 --> 00:28:31,300
He seems to have another opinion about that
他似乎对这事有另外的看法

211
00:28:32,700 --> 00:28:34,900
What did you tell him about me?
你怎么对他说我的

212
00:28:37,100 --> 00:28:39,000
Everything I know! Nothing...
所有我知道的，其实也没什么

213
00:28:39,500 --> 00:28:40,800
And it doesn't interest me
我对这不感兴趣

214
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:43,200
You know, Frank...
你知道的，弗兰克

215
00:28:43,300 --> 00:28:46,400
I think my father knows more about you
than you yourself, I'm sure about that
我认为我爸比你自己更了解你  我确信这一点

216
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:48,600
There's nothing to know about me
没有谁能了解我

217
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,600
I don't understand you, Frank
我不明白你的意思，弗兰克

218
00:28:51,100 --> 00:28:52,600
You really can be content
你真的能够胜任

219
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:55,500
My father sends you to Rome with an
important mission
我爸委你重任，派你到罗马

220
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:58,500
There are people who wait their
whole lives for a chance like that
很多人一辈子都在等那样的一个机会

221
00:28:58,800 --> 00:29:00,300
He trusts you, Frank
他信任你，弗兰克

222
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:02,800
And he even entrusts you his daughter
他甚至放心将他的女儿交给你

223
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:10,400
If you two think you can do with me whatever
you want, then you're wrong
如果你们父女俩认为可以对我为所欲为  我想你们错了

224
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:23,800
- There's Monika
- We'll sit at the bar over there
那是莫妮卡  我们坐在那边

225
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:28,700
- Good evening
- Good evening
晚上好  晚上好

226
00:29:33,600 --> 00:29:35,300
Nice dress
衣服真漂亮

227
00:29:35,400 --> 00:29:36,600
You like it?
你喜欢吗？

228
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:42,000
We're going to Rome the day after tomorrow
我们后天要去罗马

229
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,000
Do you want to dance?
你想跳舞吗？

230
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:05,000
Who is that?
那是谁？

231
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:07,500
Shall we dance, too?
我们也跳舞吗?

232
00:31:23,700 --> 00:31:24,800
Senorina?
Senorina?

233
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:27,000
Monaco
莫妮卡

234
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:34,700
Dad...
爸

235
00:31:56,100 --> 00:31:57,700
What did you tell your father?
你跟你爸说了什么？

236
00:31:58,700 --> 00:32:00,300
I told him where we are
我告诉她我们在哪儿

237
00:32:01,800 --> 00:32:03,000
Is he anxious for his money?
他担心他的钱吗？

238
00:32:04,600 --> 00:32:05,500
Why should he?
为什么担心呢？

239
00:32:06,100 --> 00:32:08,500
- If I disappeared with it
- Because of 100,000 Marks?
如果我带着钱消失的话  就因为十万马克？

240
00:32:10,700 --> 00:32:11,700
Would that be profitable?
那样有好处吗？

241
00:32:12,300 --> 00:32:13,500
Of course not for you
对你来说当然没有

242
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:15,800
What the hell is your problem?
你到底出了什么问题？

243
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:18,200
My father gives you a chance and
you're playing up here
我爸给了你一个机会  你却在这里闹

244
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:23,400
I don't need your chance
我不需要你的机会

245
00:32:23,800 --> 00:32:25,000
Are you ready now?
你准备好了吗？

246
00:33:27,900 --> 00:33:30,000
- You have to drive to the right!
- I know Rome!
你得靠右边开  我了解罗马

247
00:33:30,600 --> 00:33:31,800
Then drive correctly
那就正确的行驶

248
00:34:24,700 --> 00:34:25,800
Don't you want to call?
你不想打电话吗？

249
00:34:29,600 --> 00:34:30,500
I've got time for that
我还有时间

250
00:34:49,800 --> 00:34:50,700
Mister Cameron?
卡梅隆先生？

251
00:34:51,500 --> 00:34:53,300
Gruhner sends me, where can I meet you?
格努派我来的，在哪儿能找到你？

252
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:56,900
What's the Club called?
俱乐部叫什么？

253
00:34:59,700 --> 00:35:00,700
I'll be there at 11p.m.
晚上十一点我会到那儿

254
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:37,500
You called me Monika
你叫我莫妮卡

255
00:35:59,500 --> 00:36:01,700
When's the next plane to Mexico City?
下一班到墨西哥的飞机几点？

256
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:09,000
Please book a seat on the name Fran Murnau
请以弗兰克・马努的名义预订一张票

257
00:36:13,100 --> 00:36:15,700
36-36-107
36-36-107

258
00:36:30,900 --> 00:36:32,000
Do you want to stay here?
你想待在这儿吗？

259
00:36:34,100 --> 00:36:35,000
What did you say?
你说什么？

260
00:36:36,500 --> 00:36:37,300
Are you nervous?
紧张吗？

261
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:41,300
What shall we do until 11?
十一点前我们做些什么？

262
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:43,500
We should eat something
我们应该吃点儿什么

263
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:48,600
Let's go
走吧

264
00:36:50,400 --> 00:36:51,100
Let's go
走

265
00:38:28,100 --> 00:38:28,900
Cameron
卡梅隆

266
00:38:36,700 --> 00:38:38,000
I've awaited you yesterday
我昨天就开始等你了

267
00:38:39,300 --> 00:38:41,000
We've been waiting for half an hour
我们已经等了半小时了

268
00:38:49,600 --> 00:38:50,600
You are Laura
你是劳拉

269
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:53,900
Where are we going?
我们去哪儿？

270
00:38:55,900 --> 00:38:56,600
To my place
到我家

271
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:01,600
Later
等等

272
00:39:03,900 --> 00:39:05,300
Why have I never seen you?
为什么我从未见过你？

273
00:39:06,300 --> 00:39:07,400
I'm often in Rome
我总是在罗马

274
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:36,200
Help yourself
请随便

275
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:16,200
Put yourself together
庄重点

276
00:42:16,900 --> 00:42:18,100
Get me something to drink
给我来点喝的

277
00:42:32,200 --> 00:42:33,100
Do you want to drink something?
你想喝点儿什么吗？

278
00:42:33,900 --> 00:42:34,800
Where's the bathroom?
洗手间在哪儿？

279
00:45:12,600 --> 00:45:13,400
Mr Cameron?
卡梅隆先生？

280
00:45:13,600 --> 00:45:14,400
I'll be right with you
我马上就来

281
00:45:25,800 --> 00:45:26,800
Have you slept well?
睡得好吗？

282
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:38,200
I don't have the money
我没有钱

283
00:48:36,200 --> 00:48:37,800
I'm going to fly to Mexico, to Monika
我要飞到墨西哥，去找莫妮卡

284
00:48:39,000 --> 00:48:39,700
I love her
我爱她

285
00:48:41,800 --> 00:48:43,300
She's waiting in Acapulco
她在阿尔普尔科等我

286
00:50:00,300 --> 00:50:01,600
Everything's all right, Dad
一切都很好，爸爸

287
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:05,600
I'll come home soon
我很快回家

288
00:57:45,200 --> 00:57:46,200
Get in
进来

289
00:58:18,100 --> 00:58:20,200
During the Easter week, half of Mexico
comes here
在复活节周，一般的墨西哥人都会来这儿

290
00:58:22,500 --> 00:58:23,800
That's no fun
那没意思

291
00:58:25,600 --> 00:58:28,300
You can fly here directly from the US now
你现在可以直接从这儿飞往美国了

292
00:58:29,400 --> 00:58:30,400
Directly to here
直接到这儿

293
00:58:32,700 --> 00:58:34,800
Soon you can't spend your money nowhere anymore
很快你就不能在这儿的任何地方花你的钱了

294
00:58:38,100 --> 00:58:39,300
Nothing against communism
谁都不反对共产主义

295
00:58:40,200 --> 00:58:41,900
But if everybody can afford everything...
但是如果每个人都有用不完的钱

296
00:58:43,000 --> 00:58:44,300
Where's the deeper meaning?
更深层的意义在哪儿呢？

297
00:58:46,300 --> 00:58:49,300
Mr Wayne says he could then as well stay in Florida
韦恩先生说如果那样他还不如待在佛罗里达

298
00:58:49,400 --> 00:58:50,200
Who is Wayne?
谁是韦恩？

299
00:58:50,900 --> 00:58:52,100
You're going to meet him
你马上就会见到他的

300
00:59:40,600 --> 00:59:41,700
Frank Murnau...
弗兰克 马努

301
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:52,200
Go now
走开

302
01:00:04,900 --> 01:00:06,200
Where are the documents?
文件呢？

303
01:00:12,600 --> 01:00:13,600
How much do you pay?
你打算付多少？

304
01:00:16,500 --> 01:00:18,200
I keep my promises
我信守承诺

305
01:00:18,600 --> 01:00:20,100
50,000 Dollars
五万美元

306
01:00:27,700 --> 01:00:28,200
No
不

307
01:00:31,800 --> 01:00:33,700
That's a nice price for you
对你来说那是个不错的价格了

308
01:00:48,200 --> 01:00:50,000
You told Monika another sum
你告诉莫妮卡的是另外一个价钱

309
01:00:52,200 --> 01:00:53,100
I did
确实

310
01:00:59,100 --> 01:01:00,200
Where is Monika?
莫妮卡在哪儿？

311
01:01:46,600 --> 01:01:47,400
Come
过来

312
01:01:59,900 --> 01:02:02,400
He only wants to pay 50,000
他只想给五万

313
01:02:07,100 --> 01:02:09,500
Do you seriously believe he'll give
you half a million?
你真的相信她会给你五十万？

314
01:02:25,900 --> 01:02:27,000
You are tired
你太累了

315
01:02:32,400 --> 01:02:33,200
Wayne
韦恩

316
01:03:21,700 --> 01:03:23,000
I want half a million
我想要五十万

317
01:03:25,000 --> 01:03:26,000
Do what you want to do
随便你怎么样

318
01:04:10,100 --> 01:04:11,900
He wants half a million
他想要五十万

319
01:08:41,600 --> 01:08:43,200
I killed Cameron
我杀了卡梅隆

320
01:08:44,400 --> 01:08:45,500
Why are you telling me that?
为什么要告诉我这个？

321
01:08:48,700 --> 01:08:49,700
Because I love you
因为我爱你

322
01:08:54,600 --> 01:08:56,600
Wayne is dangerous, take the money
韦恩很危险，拿着这钱

323
01:08:57,100 --> 01:08:59,700
- I booked a seat for you in the next plane
- No!
我为你预定了下班飞机的票   不

324
01:09:04,000 --> 01:09:05,700
I don't want no more, leave me alone
我什么都不想要了，让我静静

325
01:15:12,400 --> 01:15:14,100
He doesn't have the key
他没有钥匙

